@ptn・8 just reiterating to make it perfectly clear, high risk martingale strategies will be deprioritized through risk analysis in a feature being developed. This has been in the works. If your strategy relies on martingale it will perform poorly & be deprioritized by the network.

While our SN’s native incentive mechanism already handles downtrends of martingale strategies and deprioritizes them while maintaining their gains (for the purpose of a native strategy), we want to be clear we will be proactive in identifying & deprioritizing high risk strategies through analysis. Thank you.

(Please review my messages with Sami to better understand the native strategy that already handles martingale strategies using incentive)

@τravis | τAO τemplar A 1x position means that you put the full weight of the portfolio against the position. It also means that any movement on the position will directly translate to your portfolio returns and max drawdown (with fees), both of which are used to calculate your risk adjusted return. A 1% loss on a 1x position would result in a 1% MDD, while a 5x position on the same 1% loss would result in a 5% MDD.

We don’t have guardrails to place like SL/TP yet, so you’ll need to manage risk by actively closing your positions or reducing leverage. Our incentive system prioritizes miner drawdown values between 0.25% and 1.5%, you’ll likely do well by selecting a drawdown within this range and attempt to keep your drawdown below this value with your strategy. Our top miners typically use a more realistic range between 0.1x and 3x leverage, also depends on the trade pair.

Miner intro docs have more details: https://docs.taoshi.io/ptn/miner/overview/

